package org.hibernate.sql.exec.internal;

import org.hibernate.metamodel.mapping.SqlTypedMapping;

public class TemporalJdbcParameter extends SqlTypedMappingJdbcParameter {

    public TemporalJdbcParameter(SqlTypedMapping sqlTypedMapping) {
        super( sqlTypedMapping );
    }
}
```

**Construction & fields:** `TemporalJdbcParameter` is a minimal subclass of `SqlTypedMappingJdbcParameter`, which in turn extends `AbstractJdbcParameter`. It holds no additional fields — just delegates to the parent constructor with a `SqlTypedMapping`. The parent class (`SqlTypedMappingJdbcParameter`) stores the `sqlTypedMapping` and also calls `super(sqlTypedMapping.getJdbcMapping())` to establish the JDBC mapping. Through the hierarchy, the key inherited member is `private final JdbcMapping jdbcMapping` from `AbstractJdbcParameter`.

